<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-07-10T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-07-10T19:00:00-05:00" n="777" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d777">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">751R.62114/7–644: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            Secretary in Charge of the Mission at Algiers</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Lawton</hi></persName>)</head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-07-10T20:00:00-04:00">July 10,
                                1944—8 p.m.</date>
                        </dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>2161. Your 2287, July 6. Please point out to Massigli that this Government
                        takes an extremely serious view of the reports of the execution of the six
                        German prisoners of war and of the sanctioning <pb facs="1251" n="1237" xml:id="pg_1237"/> of the incident by the French authorities in North
                        Africa. The American Government is greatly concerned lest these reprisals
                        lead to counter reprisals by the German authorities against American and
                        Allied prisoners of war. Please report the reply which Massigli makes to
                        your representations.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>